    <!-- QUICK ANSWER -->
    <div class="callout">
      <strong>The honest short answer:</strong> The supplementation safety database during pregnancy is too limited to give a definitive yes or no. Creatine is a naturally occurring compound that pregnant women consume safely through diet (1-2g daily from meat and fish). Supplemental doses (3-5g+ daily) have not been adequately studied in human pregnancy. Animal research and emerging human data suggest possible neuroprotective benefits for the fetus, but no formal supplementation recommendation exists. The conservative, widely-recommended approach is to pause supplementation during pregnancy and breastfeeding, and resume after weaning. Always discuss with your OB-GYN.
