    <p>Creatine has become one of the most-searched supplements among women in 2026, and the question of pregnancy safety is increasingly common. Search demand for "creatine while pregnant" exceeds 2,900 monthly queries in the US alone. The honest answer requires acknowledging both what the research has investigated and the substantial gaps in human clinical data — which is exactly what this guide does.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
      <span class="key-stat-num">1-2g</span>
